SIMPLE: finery
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Finery
<hw>Fin"er*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Fineness;
beauty.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Don't choose your place of study by the <qex>finery</qex> of the
prospects.</q> <rj><qau>I. Watts.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Ornament; decoration; especially, excecially
decoration; showy clothes; jewels.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her mistress' cast-off <qex>finery</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>F. W.
Robertson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <ety>[Cf. <er>Refinery</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Iron
Works)</fld> <def>A charcoal hearth or furnace for the conversion of
cast iron into wrought iron, or into iron suitable for
puddling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Finespun</ent>⟦br⟧
